-- First Solar, EDF Energies Delay Plant Construction, Echos Says
-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 2010-12-17T07:45:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/first-solar-edf-energies-delay-plant-construction-echos-says.html
First Solar Inc. has delayed the
start of construction of a solar panel factory near Bordeaux,
France because of questions about French regulations,  Les Echos 
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer  Rob Gillette .  First Solar and EDF Energies Nouvelles SA said in July 2009
that they planned to build the plant, reaching full production
in the second half of 2011. The project may be canceled,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Tara Patel  in Paris at 
 tpatel2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
